SYMPTOM_TEXT: I have had my period since I was 13 years old, and I am now 20, almost 21 in four days. I am fully up to date with all my vaccines and have NEVER had an effect like this before. Since the second dose of my Pfizer vaccine, I got my period four days after, which was normal at day 31. After this immediate period, my periods have been REMARKABLY LATE FOR THE PAST THREE, ALMOST FOUR MONTHS. Once this initial period was over, it took me 50 days to get my next period, and I am now on day 40 with no period. For the past seven years, my periods have been EXTREMELY regular like clockwork, 28-32 days every month. I called my OBGYN office, as I thought I must be pregnant even though I cannot recall engaging in vaginal intercourse. They told me if I skipped two cycles then I should come in and get checked out, and to take another pregnancy test the next week. I ended up taking five pregnancy tests, and they were all negative. I have tracked my periods on an app on my phone for years, and I have never been this late in my entire life. I am not exceedingly stressed, I am not strenuously exercising, I am not taking part in any sexual activity that would lead to pregnancy- I am not doing anything I can think of that would make my periods late. I cannot imagine any other reason for why my periods have been irregular for the past three months other than the Pfizer vaccine as this effect started after I received this vaccination. I have read accounts of this happening with other women, but only for one cycle. This has now not only effected me for one cycle but now two, and I am growing increasingly concerned. I will be bringing this up with my OBGYN.

Thirteen days after the vaccine I began to experience symptoms like when I had COVID. On day 13 I started to itch and my BP dropped and I became light headed. My vision started to go and I had a hard time breathing and forming words for my husband to help me with some water. This lasted about 20 min.    Since then I have been having heart rate increases up into the 150s with minimal effort. Bending like doing dishes or putting away groceries makes me extremely light headed. I have become so tired just folding a little bit of laundry. It wasn?t until a few weeks in that I noticed this was all exactly like when I had COVID. Including being okay in the morning but having so many issues by the evening. So weird.   I?m 3 weeks and 4 days past my second shot and finally starting to have some better days again but no day has been symptom free. I wish could know if this is happening to other long haulers and that it will most likely resolve, I have been starting to wonder about disability and really having a hard time facing the fact that I no longer can complete simple house hold chores like I used to.
LAB_DATA: I had so many tests prior to the vaccine. Since then I have just been following up with my neurologist and she referred me to medical centers long hauler clinic with autonomic dysfunction and Postural Orthostatic Hypotention.
CUR_ILL: Considered a covid Long Hauler, with autonomic instability since catching covid December 2020.  I am under the care of a neurologist and have documented everything with her.
HISTORY: My covid symptoms led me to the diagnosis of Hypermobility Spectrum Disorder (EDS), Mast Cell Activation Syndrome, Autonomic Dysfunction with Postural Orthostatic Hypotention, confirmed via tilt table.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I took the vaccine on April 6th around 8:40 PM, and the next day around 2:30 AM I noticed multiple pumps on my chest area and the back part of my thighs, and they were quite itchy. On April 8th, I woke up with my lips completely swollen, very tingly, and feeling warm - I, unfortunately, had a college test on that exact day and could not go to the hospital straight away. They told me to go get it checked and go to the hospital in case I have trouble breathing. My lips ended up going back to normal eventually. I went to three different doctors after a couple of days because I kept getting sick and also to explain the situation and ask if I could even take the second dose of the vaccine since it was approaching. All three doctors told me not to because my body could go into anaphylactic shock, so I did not take it.
"Covid arm"- large and red raised patch on skin. Warm to touch with minimal itching and pain.

On May 13th my right arm (where I got the shot) was in extreme pain as of this report it hasn't gotten much better..

I experienced numbness in my right hand. It switched between my hand and 2 middle fingers. Since I have had covid, my nose would run off and on. My head would hurt and I always had some type of congestion and high bpm. When I received the shot, my congestion and runny nose dried up. It felt as if the shot was pulling something through my veins and drying up the congestion instantly and clearing up my head congestion as well.
large painful lymph nodes above and below left clavicle,

3 days after vaccine on left arm, woke up with large bumps covering right arm. Throughout the day, the rash/bumps worsened and spread over my whole body. That night, aches/chills began. The next day the rash was very severe, red bumps covering body, with it slowly spreading up next onto face. Most concentrated and severe on stomach, sides, upper thighs and creases of knees, buttocks, elbows. That day, aches and chills were severe  and could not get out of bed. Heavy chest occurred later that day. These symptoms lasted 2-3 days, with the rash lasting over a week. Doctor prescribed oral steroids (30 pills total) to get rash under control.  Also had lack of appetite and bad headaches

After 4 days left upper arm started hurting and kept hurting worse. Went to clinic due to pain and received injection. Continues to hurt and returned to clinic and received medication for pain and muscle relaxer. Returned 5/22/21 due to continued pain and was sent to get ultrasound. To follow up with Orthropedic Doctor on May 24,2021.

I had 3 stages of reactions to the first dose. 1. Same day of the vaccine, I had a mild soreness in my arm which was normal for a vaccine shot. Nothing out of the ordinary. 2. Second day, I felt tired, similar to what I would feel if I am getting  the flu. I felt as if I had a elevated body temperature, but the forehead thermometer was normal. 3. Third day, I felt better overall, only had the soreness in the arm left. 4. Day 12, I noticed 3 patches of a rash on and around the injection site. I only noticed them because I felt my arm warmer than usual. The texture of the rash is a bit different than my regular skin, mildly reddish in color, 1 patch is 2 inches in diameter, the others are smaller. I called in to vaccination team and the nurse took my statement and directed me to report it here.

Received shot on 5/17/2021 at 1:00...Within 20 to 30 minutes upon receiving the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine, I experienced numbness on the right side of my entire body where the vaccine was given, also and pressure behind my right eye. Along with tingling on the right side of my body, headache, fatigue.  Called pharmacy and was advised by a man that it?s fairly common and that it would go away in 24-48 hours and if it didn?t then to seek medical care.   As of 12:40AM on 05/22/2021 it is better but still not back to fully 100%.  It is now been 4 days going on 5 and I still have loss of sensation on the right side of my body of approximately 5% (tingling).  Have not taken anything nor sought medical care. Even thought a visit to the ER was recommended, Patient said he could still mostly function.

After administering the shot, patient was very quiet. As I was filling out the rest of her paperwork, I asked her a question that she did not respond to, I noticed her sweating and start to fall forward. I was able to catch her, guard her head and lie her down, but she seemed to be seizing (clenching and unclenching her arms and feet, her eyes had rolled back, with teeth clenching ). She did not acknowledge when I called her name, but was making small noises. It lasted for a little over a minute before her vision was able to focus on me. I asked if she was alright, told her that she passed out and may have had a seizure; then I asked if she would like me to call an ambulance. She declined multiple time and stated that she fainted sometimes when she was scared (although never before with an immunization and no history of seizure, as was listed on the VAR). I offered her water (she declined) and to take her blood pressure (she declined) and told her to wait in the waiting room for at least 15 minutes while we monitored her. Patient was joined by her aunt (who was waiting for her outside) and I suggested that they make an appointment with patient's regular doctor, which patient again declined.  I settled them in, then checked on her at minute 5 and minute 10, she stated that she was "feeling fine" at both checks (no sweating or seizure signs either). When I went back to check at minute 15, they were already gone. Patient did not return my phone calls for follow-up later in the day.

Feels as if ears will burst if I lean over. Headache in forehead. Fever 99.0 -99.4.  Ear pressure aching ringing has continued since. At times, left ear feels like a void like I can?t hear. Right ear like it hears too well too loud. Music songs sound different. Like not blended. Like missing a part. When 2 many sounds happening, I can?t distinguish detail. It?s all blurred. An ambulance went by. I couldn?t hear with my left ear. Seatbelt beeping in car is faint and does not bother me now.

About 30 minutes of still not feeling well I had watery stools immediately followed by vomiting, hot and cold flashes, and profusely sweating all over. Seizure; Syncope; Diarrhoea; Chills; Vomiting; This case VAERS (Reference number: 0989940) on 11-May-2021 and was forwarded to Moderna on 11-May-2021.    This regulatory authority case was reported by an other health care professional and describes the occurrence of SEIZURE (Seizure) and SYNCOPE (Syncope) in a 30-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below.     The patient's past medical history included Epilepsy. Concurrent medical conditions included Drug allergy (sulfa). Concomitant products included LAMOTRIGINE, PHENYTOIN SODIUM (DILANTIN D.A.) and LEVONORGESTREL (MIRENA) for an unknown indication.    On 19-Jan-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 19-Jan-2021, the patient experienced SEIZURE (Seizure) (seriousness criterion medically significant), SYNCOPE (Syncope) (seriousness criterion medically significant), DIARRHOEA (Diarrhoea), CHILLS (Chills) and VOMITING (Vomiting). At the time of the report, SEIZURE (Seizure), SYNCOPE (Syncope), DIARRHOEA (Diarrhoea), CHILLS (Chills) and VOMITING (Vomiting) had resolved.        The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown.   For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments.   Patient experienced profuse vomiting and diarrhea, syncope, chills, seizures. Emergency room visit received 3 bags of lactated ringers, 12 mg of IV zofran, 12.5 mg of IV Phenergan. Full blood work and 2 computerized tomogram (CT) scans but results were not provided.  Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events of chills, vomiting, and diarrhea, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Causality for the events of seizure and syncope are probably related to the patient's medical history.; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events of chills, vomiting, and diarrhea, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Causality for the events of seizure and syncope are probably related to the patient's medical history.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Drug allergy (sulfa); Epilepsy

SYMPTOM_TEXT: myoclonic seizure; Dizziness; fever; This regulatory authority case was reported by an other health care professional and describes the occurrence of MYOCLONIC EPILEPSY (myoclonic seizure), DIZZINESS (Dizziness) and PYREXIA (fever) in a 58-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) for COVID-19 vaccination.
